'''丁吉尔'''“Dingir”（一般音译diĝir，明显的发音是{{IPA|/diŋir/}}）是一种楔形文符号，最常见于对“[[神|神]]”的指定，但它自身也有含意。作为一个限定词，它本身不发音，并且通常被译为上标“D”，如<sup>D</sup>Inanna（女神[[伊南娜|伊南娜]]）等。一般地来讲，“丁吉尔”可译为“男神”或“女神”。<ref name="DOE">Edzard, 2003</ref>

[[苏美尔|苏美尔]][[楔形文字|楔形文字]]符号（DIĜIR，[[File:Cuneiform_sumer_dingir.jpg|30px]]{{NoteTag|By assyriological convention, capitals identify a cuneiform sign, while the phonemic value of a sign in a given context is given in lower case. See also [[Sumerogram|Sumerogram]].}}本身代表了苏美尔文字（[[天|天]]或[[天堂|天堂]]<ref name="JLH">Hayes, 2000</ref>，苏美人神殿中的最高神“安”（An）和“diĝir”（神）的表意符。在[[亚述|亚述]]楔形文字中，它（安、DIĜIR，[[File:B010ellst.png|30px]]）可能既是“神”（ilum）的表意符，又是安或“ìl-”的音节书写符。在[[赫梯|赫梯]]拼法中，该符号的音节值是再加一个“An。

[[苏美尔|苏美尔]]文化中“神”的概念与“天”有关，因为楔形文字中两个这样的符号就代表了“天空”，而其原来的形状是一颗星。因此，“神”的原义是与天空中显圣的“光明”或“光亮”相联系的。[[苏美尔|苏美尔]]的“丁吉尔”被认为可能与[[突厥|突厥]]的[[腾格里|腾格里]]“天空，天堂”有关的一个[[外来语|外来词]]。<ref>[[Mircea_Eliade|Mircea Eliade]], John C. Holt, ''Patterns in comparative religion'', 1958, p. 94. The connection of ''dingir'' and Old Turkic ''tengere'' was made by F. Hommel in ''Grundriss der Geographie und Geschichte des alten Orients'' (1928).
P. A. Barton in ''Semitic and Hamitic Origins'' (1934) suggested that the Mesopotamian sky god [[Anu_(mythology)|Anu]] may have been imported from Central Asia to Mesopotamia. 
The similarity of ''dingir'' and ''tengri'' was noted as early as 1862 (i.e. during the early phase of the decipherment of the Sumerian language, before even the term Sumerian had been coined to refer to it),  by [[George_Rawlinson|George Rawlinson]] in his ''The Five Great Monarchies of the Ancient Eastern World'' (p. 78).</ref>

